#: src/administration/theming.md:1
msgid "Theming Guide"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/theming.md:3
msgid "Bootstrap"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/theming.md:5
msgid ""
"Lemmy uses [Bootstrap v5](https://getbootstrap.com/), and very few custom "
"css classes, so any bootstrap v5 compatible theme should work fine. Use a "
"tool like [bootstrap.build](https://bootstrap.build/) to create a bootstrap "
"v5 theme. Export the `bootstrap.min.css` once you're done, and save the "
"`_variables.scss` too."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/theming.md:7
msgid "Custom Theme Directory"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/theming.md:9
msgid ""
"If you installed Lemmy with Docker, save your theme file to `./volumes/lemmy-"
"ui/extra_themes`. For native installation (without Docker), themes are "
"loaded by lemmy-ui from ./extra_themes folder. A different path can be "
"specified with LEMMY_UI_EXTRA_THEMES_FOLDER environment variable."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/theming.md:11
msgid ""
"After a theme is added, users can select it under `/settings`. Admins can "
"set a theme as site default under `/admin`."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/theming.md:13
msgid "Default Theme Locations"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/theming.md:15
msgid ""
"Default Lemmy themes are located in `/lemmy-ui/src/assets/css/themes`. Atom "
"themes used for styling `<code>` are in `/lemmy-ui/src/assets/css/code-"
"themes`. Custom css classes and changes to the default Bootstrap styles are "
"in `/lemmy-ui/src/assets/css/main.css`."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/theming.md:17
msgid "Making CSS Themes with Sass and Bootstrap"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/theming.md:19
msgid "Some tips if making a theme based off the default Lemmy themes."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/theming.md:21
msgid "Every theme has these files:"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/theming.md:23
msgid "an output `theme.css`"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/theming.md:24
msgid "an output `theme.css.map`"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/theming.md:25
msgid "`theme.scss`"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/theming.md:26
msgid "`_variables.theme.scss`"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/theming.md:28
msgid ""
"All `_variables.theme.scss` files will inherit variables from `_variables."
"scss`. All `theme.scss` will import bootstrap variables from `\"../../../../"
"node_modules/bootstrap/scss/bootstrap\";` and its `_variables.theme.scss` "
"file. It may import additional variables from another theme if it is built "
"off it. For example, `litely-compact.scss` imports from `_variables.litely."
"scss`."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/theming.md:31
msgid "Using SCSS Files"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/theming.md:33
msgid ""
"If you are new to Sass, keep in mind that `theme.scss` files are for css and "
"Sass flavored css. `_variables.theme.scss` are for variables."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/theming.md:35
msgid "Export Your CSS File"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/theming.md:37
msgid ""
"To export your custom `.scss` and `_variables.theme.scss` files to a `.css` "
"file open the command line in the same directory as your files and run: "
"`sass theme.scss theme.css` which will generate the `.css` and `.css.map` "
"files."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/theming.md:40
msgid "Bootstrap Notes"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/theming.md:42
msgid ""
"If you are new to Bootstrap, be aware that variables starting with a dollar "
"sign like `$variable` are Bootstrap variables and when output to css will "
"look like `--bs-variable`. You can also define custom root variables in your "
"`_variables.theme.scss` files like `:root {--custom-variable: value;};` and "
"you can refer to this again in your `theme.scss` file."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/theming.md:44
msgid "Bootstrap Variables on Lemmy"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/theming.md:46
msgid ""
"The Darkly and Litely themes use default Bootstrap variables to define the "
"grayscales and colours. Inspecting the Bootstrap documentation for how "
"colours are applied to elements is recommended, along with inspecting the "
"CSS and output files."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/theming.md:48
msgid "Light and Dark Modes"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/theming.md:50
msgid ""
"Even though `darkly.css` is a dark theme, it has in-built light and dark "
"modes using media queries. The Bootstrap variables `$enable-dark-mode` and "
"`$enable-light-mode` can be used to toggle this behaviour on or off."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/theming.md:52
msgid "Overwriting Variables"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/theming.md:54
msgid ""
"Most Lemmy theming is done with Bootstrap's default variables. Some "
"variables are defined with `!important` which means if you have defined them "
"in your custom theme that unless it also has `!important` it will be "
"overwritten. To check, do a search in one of the default theme files or use "
"the Developer Tools in your browser."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/theming.md:56
msgid ""
"To quickly test your theme if you do not own a Lemmy instance, you can use a "
"browser add on to load your custom CSS file."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/theming.md:58
msgid "External Stylesheets"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/theming.md:60
msgid ""
"As users cannot currently upload their own themes in Settings (only Admin "
"can do that), custom themes loaded with an external style sheet will need to "
"take into account that users will have a pre-selected theme in Settings that "
"may have conflicting styles with the custom theme. If a theme is developed "
"from an existing theme, having the default theme selected in Settings can "
"minimize style conflicts."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/theming.md:62
msgid "How CSS Themes are Added to Settings"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/theming.md:64
msgid ""
"In short, given the css theme is the correct file format and in the correct "
"theme directory, it will be appended to the bottom of the theme list in "
"Settings. The name is the filename minus the file extension. Details are "
"below."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/theming.md:66
msgid "CSS Format Check"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/theming.md:68
msgid ""
"The Typescript file `theme-handler.ts` in `/lemmy-ui/src/server/handlers/` "
"will check for existing `css` files from the custom theme folder (`./volumes/"
"lemmy-ui/extra_themes` or `./extra_themes`). Non `css` files will trigger an "
"error."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/theming.md:70
msgid "Building the Theme List"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/theming.md:72
msgid ""
"If a custom css theme is found, the handler will call `themes-list-handler."
"ts` which will load `build-themes-list.ts` from `/lemmy-ui/src/server/utils/"
"`. The file `build-themes-list.ts` will search the directories for files "
"ending in `.css` and build a list."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/theming.md:74
msgid "Custom themes are appended to the bottom of the theme list."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/theming.md:76
msgid "Theme Names"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/theming.md:78
msgid ""
"`build-themes-list.ts` will remove the file extension `.css` from the theme "
"filename to display in Settings. For example, `darkly-compact.css` will "
"appear as `darkly-compact`."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/theming.md:80
msgid "Build and Format Theme Files Quickly"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/theming.md:82
msgid ""
"Some tips to save time which would be useful for theme developers or if you "
"are submitting pull requests to [lemmy-ui (Github)](https://github.com/"
"LemmyNet/lemmy-ui)."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/theming.md:84
msgid "After changing variables or Sass files:"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/theming.md:86
msgid ""
"run `pnpm themes:build` to automatically rebuild all Lemmy css theme files "
"using Sass"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/theming.md:87
msgid ""
"run `npx prettier -w /lemmy-ui/src/assets/css/themes` to reformat the code "
"in the themes directory with prettier"
msgstr ""

