#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:21
msgid ""
"```\n"
"proxy_http_version 1.1;\n"
"proxy_set_header Upgrade $http_upgrade;\n"
"proxy_set_header Connection \"upgrade\";\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:27
msgid "Rate limit error when many users access the site"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:29
msgid ""
"Check that the headers `X-Real-IP` and `X-Forwarded-For` are sent to Lemmy "
"by the reverse proxy. Otherwise, it will count all actions towards the rate "
"limit of the reverse proxy's IP. In nginx it should look like this:"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:39
msgid "Other instances can't fetch local objects (community, post, etc)"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:41
msgid ""
"Your reverse proxy (eg nginx) needs to forward requests with header `Accept: "
"application/activity+json` to the backend. This is handled by the following "
"lines:"
