#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:122
msgid "You don't receive actions reliably"
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:124
msgid ""
"Due to the lemmy queue, remote lemmy instances will be sending apub sync "
"actions serially to you. If your server rate of processing them is slower "
"than the rate the origin server is sending them, when visiting the [lemmy-"
"federation-state](https://phiresky.github.io/lemmy-federation-state/site) "
"for the remote server, you'll see your instance in the \"lagging behind\" "
"section."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:126
msgid ""
"This can be avoided by setting the config value `federation."
"concurrent_sends_per_instance` to a value greater than 1 on the sending "
"instance."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:128
msgid ""
"Typically the speed at which you process an incoming action should be less "
"than 100ms. If this is higher, this might signify problems with your "
"database performance or your networking setup."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:130
msgid ""
"Note that even apub action ingestion speed which seems sufficient for most "
"other instances, might become insufficient if the origin server is receiving "
"actions from their userbase faster than you can process them. I.e. if the "
"origin server receives 10 actions per second, but you can only process 8 "
"actions per second, you'll inevitably start falling behind that one server "
"only."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:132
msgid "These steps might help you diagnose this."
