#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:224
msgid ""
"If you notice that your lemmy-ui sometimes becomes sluggish or unresponsive "
"over a period of minutes/hours and then it passes, you might be getting "
"targeted by scraping bots."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:226
msgid ""
"There's a lot of scraping bots online and they can easily overwhelm your "
"site when they're behaving too \"greedily\". Unfortunately the existing "
"lemmy-ui has a habit of falling over when polled too eagerly, while the "
"backend still continues to work."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:228
msgid ""
"A solution is to cache responses in nginx as seen in lemmy-ansible [here]"
"(https://github.com/LemmyNet/lemmy-ansible/blob/1.5.3/templates/nginx."
"conf#L2-L3) and [here](https://github.com/LemmyNet/lemmy-ansible/blob/1.5.3/"
"templates/nginx.conf#L66-L71). This way lemmy-ui doesn't have to generate "
"all responses from scratch, which reduces CPU load. However it won't help if "
"a single crawler goes through thousands of unique urls in a short time."
msgstr ""

#: src/administration/troubleshooting.md:230
